                                             Maiden Erlegh  Trust     Menu  Close    Home About Us Governance News and Events Vacancies Contact Us       Select Language            About Us  Home About Us Statutory Documentation Gender Pay Gap      Gender Pay Gap  Maiden Erlegh Trust is an employer required by law to carry out Gender Pay Reporting under the Equality Act 2010 (Gender Pay Gap Information) Regulations 2017.  This involves carrying out six calculations that show the difference between the average earnings of men and women in our organisation but does not involve publishing pay data for individual employees.  We must publish this report annually by 30 March.      Maiden Erlegh Trust - Gender Pay Gap Report 2017 pdf File     In This Section  Admission Arrangements Articles of Association Financial Statements Funding Agreements Gender Pay Gap          High Visibility Version  |  Sitemap Website by e4education  | Copyright © 2018 Maiden Erlegh Trust            